CARMEN SAECULARE.

An ode written, by command of Augustus, to be sung in public at the Ludi Saeculares, a grand religious ceremony intended to celebrate the inauguration of the new regime. The proposal to hold such a celebration was first made in 13.c. 23, but it was not carried out till the summer of B.c. 17.
